article.headline: Texas-Pan American 56, N.C. Central 50
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa -- Emmanuel Jones scored 10 points in the second half to help Texas-Pan American rally to a 56-50 victory over North Carolina Central on Sunday in the consolation championship of the Iowa Realty Invitational. Jones had 16 rebounds, seven offensive, for the Broncs (3-6), who trailed 25-18 at halftime. Ben Smith and Nathan Hawkins each had nine points for Texas-Pan American, which finished with a 39-26 rebound advantage. Stevy Worah-Ozimo scored 14 points to lead the Eagles (0-9), while Vincent Davis added 13. The Broncs shot 28 percent from the field in the first half, then rallied to shoot 54 percent, including three 3-pointers, in the second.
